NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

04:43.584 --> 04:47.721
FINE. I'LL GO LOOK HER UP
IN THE PHONE BOOK.

04:47.721 --> 04:51.024
I MEAN, HOW MANY LOPEZES
CAN THERE BE IN L.A.?

04:51.024 --> 04:53.494
PLEASE TELL ME HER NUMBER.

04:53.494 --> 04:54.862
GEORGE, IT SEEMS LIKE

04:54.862 --> 04:57.831
WAYNE IS PRETTY DETERMINED
TO TALK TO YOUR MOM.

04:57.831 --> 05:01.435
MAYBE IT'S TIME HE KNEW
WHAT WAS GOING ON.

05:01.435 --> 05:03.937
YEAH. (clears throat)

05:03.937 --> 05:06.674
YOU'RE RIGHT. UM...

05:06.674 --> 05:09.209
I-I DIDN'T--I DIDN'T WANT
TO HURT YOU, WAYNE,

05:09.209 --> 05:12.680
BUT, UH, MY MOM'S DEAD.

05:12.680 --> 05:15.383
OH, NO.
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

05:16.684 --> 05:19.687
MAYBE YOU SHOULD TELL WAYNE
HOW YOUR MOM DIED.

05:19.687 --> 05:22.089
YOU DON'T THINK
I CAN DO THAT?

05:22.089 --> 05:25.793
SHE SMOKED AND DRANK
FOR SO LONG, WAYNE,

05:25.793 --> 05:30.464
THAT SHE HAD
A MYO-CARDENAS INFECTION.

05:30.464 --> 05:32.800
DON'T YOU MEAN
MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION?

05:32.800 --> 05:34.502
I WISH. THAT'S TREATABLE.

05:34.502 --> 05:36.837
THE THING I SAID--
VERY DEADLY.

05:38.639 --> 05:41.775
(War's "Low Rider" playing)

05:45.446 --> 05:47.314
* ALL MY FRIENDS

05:47.314 --> 05:50.884
* KNOW THE LOW RIDER

05:52.486 --> 05:55.055
* THE LOW RIDER

05:55.055 --> 05:57.591
* IS A LITTLE HIGHER

05:59.192 --> 06:02.863
**

06:07.300 --> 06:09.302
SO, YEAH,
I MEAN, THERE IT IS.

06:09.302 --> 06:11.539
MY MOM PASSED AWAY.

06:11.539 --> 06:14.307
I'M SO SORRY.
I MEAN, AFTER MY DIVORCE,

06:14.307 --> 06:17.010
I REALLY HAD IT
WORKED UP IN MY HEAD

06:17.010 --> 06:18.846
THAT SOMEHOW I HAD A...

06:18.846 --> 06:21.114
I HAD A CHANCE
OF WINNING HER BACK.

06:21.114 --> 06:24.785
SHE WAS THE ONLY WOMAN
WHO EVER CALLED ME ON MY CRAP.

06:24.785 --> 06:26.820
SHE MADE ME A BETTER MAN.

06:26.820 --> 06:30.023
I CAN'T BELIEVE SHE'S GONE.

06:32.259 --> 06:34.628
THAT IS SO SWEET.

06:34.628 --> 06:37.865
BENNY MIGHT HAVE BEEN
REALLY HAPPY TO SEE YOU.

06:37.865 --> 06:39.332
GEORGE?

06:39.332 --> 06:42.269
ANGIE, SHE'S DEAD.
SHE'D BE HAPPY TO SEE ANYTHING.

06:42.269 --> 06:46.507
REALLY, A CLOUD, A TOMATO.
MENTION SOMETHING.
UH, A CAT?

06:46.507 --> 06:48.709
NO, BRO, SHE HATED CATS.

06:48.709 --> 06:50.744
YOU REALLY DIDN'T KNOW HER
THAT WELL, DID YOU?

06:50.744 --> 06:52.312
WELL, I GUESS NOT.

06:52.312 --> 06:55.348
WELL, IF YOU DON'T MIND, UM,
I NEED TIME TO GRIEVE...

06:55.348 --> 06:56.850
OH, I'M SORRY.

06:56.850 --> 06:58.351
INTERNALLY.
OF COURSE.

06:58.351 --> 07:01.254
DAD, GRANDMA BENNY'S
ON THE PHONE.

07:01.254 --> 07:02.990
ON THE PHONE?

07:02.990 --> 07:05.192
STUPID KID. HE KEEPS
SPILLING HER ASHES.

07:05.192 --> 07:06.494
SPONGE OFF THE PHONE

07:06.494 --> 07:09.029
AND PUT THE URN
BACK ON THE MANTEL.

07:09.029 --> 07:10.230
TAKE CARE, WAYNE.

07:10.230 --> 07:12.866
SURROUND YOURSELF
WITH FRIENDS AND FAMILY.

07:12.866 --> 07:15.869
GRANDMA'S MAD THAT YOU
KICKED HER OUT OF THE CAR.

07:15.869 --> 07:18.338
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT,
ASHES?

07:18.338 --> 07:20.741
I WAS LYING TO THAT MAN
TO PROTECT GRANDMA.

07:20.741 --> 07:24.878
WHAT IS HE, A BOOKIE?
BILL COLLECTOR? REPO MAN--

07:24.878 --> 07:26.914
MARRIED GUY
WITH AN ANGRY WIFE?

07:26.914 --> 07:30.050
ALL RIGHT. NO MORE SLEEPOVERS
AT GRANDMA'S FOR YOU.

07:34.221 --> 07:37.525
DID YOU SEE HOW CHOKED UP
WAYNE WAS ABOUT YOUR MOM?

07:37.525 --> 07:39.827
I THINK YOU SHOULD
TELL BENNY ABOUT HIM

07:39.827 --> 07:42.329
AND LET HER DECIDE
WHAT TO DO.
NO, I IF TELL HER
ABOUT WAYNE NOW,

07:42.329 --> 07:45.032
SHE'S GONNA FIND OUT THAT
I'VE BEEN LYING ABOUT HIM

07:45.032 --> 07:47.701
ALL THESE YEARS.
SHE'S GONNA FIND OUT EVENTUALLY.

07:47.701 --> 07:49.837
NO, SHE'S NOT.
YOU'RE NOT GONNA GET
AWAY WITH THIS.

07:49.837 --> 07:54.307
THE TRUTH ALWAYS COMES OUT.
NO, THE LOPEZ WAY IS YOU TAKE
YOUR SECRETS TO THE GRAVE.

07:54.307 --> 07:57.177
THEN THEY COME OUT
AT THE FUNERAL AND A BIG FIGHT.

07:57.177 --> 07:59.379
REMEMBER WHEN
MY COUSIN ROBERTO DIED,

07:59.379 --> 08:02.950
AND THE TWO WOMEN HE WAS MARRIED
TO FOUND OUT ABOUT EACH OTHER?
THAT WAS SAD.

08:02.950 --> 08:05.218
SAD? IT WAS FUNNY.
TWO WOMEN IN DRESSES

08:05.218 --> 08:07.420
WITH PAINTED-ON EYEBROWS
THROWING PUNCHES?

08:07.420 --> 08:09.222
IT WAS LIKE
MEXICAN "DYNASTY."

08:09.222 --> 08:11.925
IF YOU DON'T TELL
YOUR MOM THE TRUTH,

08:11.925 --> 08:14.528
I AM GONNA LOSE
SOME RESPECT FOR YOU.

08:14.528 --> 08:17.731
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.
WOULD YOU LOSE SO MUCH RESPECT

08:17.731 --> 08:20.400
THAT YOU WOULD LEAVE ME?
WELL, OF COURSE NOT.

08:20.400 --> 08:22.903
OKAY, THEN I'M GOOD.

08:24.404 --> 08:27.440
(can opens)
(Benny)
WHAT ARE YOU WATCHING?

08:27.440 --> 08:30.143
UH, "SportsCenter."
(clears throat)

08:30.143 --> 08:32.245
I'D STICK AROUND, BENNY,

08:32.245 --> 08:35.482
BECAUSE THERE'S
AN INTERESTING MOVIE COMING ON.

08:35.482 --> 08:38.085
IT'S BASED ON A TRUE STORY.

08:38.085 --> 08:39.920
IT'S ABOUT A MOM

08:39.920 --> 08:42.222
WHO LIED TO HER SON
HIS WHOLE LIFE,

08:42.222 --> 08:46.059
AND THEN ONE TIME,
THE SON LIES TO THE MOTHER.

08:46.059 --> 08:48.261
OH, YEAH.
I THINK I SAW IT.

08:48.261 --> 08:49.730
IT'S THE ONE WHERE

08:49.730 --> 08:52.633
FARRAH FAWCETT
LIGHTS THAT GUY ON FIRE.

08:52.633 --> 08:55.535
NO, THIS MOVIE
IS REALLY HEARTWARMING

08:55.535 --> 08:58.105
BECAUSE THE SON
FINALLY REALIZES

08:58.105 --> 09:00.908
HOW MUCH IT HURT
WHEN HE WAS LIED TO,

09:00.908 --> 09:03.577
